TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed HttpStatusCode extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: Contains the values of status codes defined for HTTP.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Net.HttpStatusCode> enumeration contains the values of the status codes defined in RFC 2616 for HTTP 1.1.
The status of an HTTP request is contained in the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebResponse.StatusCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property.
## Examples The following example compares the status returned by an <xref:System.Net.HttpWebResponse> with a member of the <xref:System.Net.HttpStatusCode> class to determine the status of a response.
[!code-cpp[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/samples/snippets/cpp/VS_Snippets_Remoting/Classic HttpStatusCode Example/CPP/source.cpp#1)] [!code-csharp[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Remoting/Classic HttpStatusCode Example/CS/source.cs#1)] [!code-vb[Classic HttpStatusCode Example#1](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_Remoting/Classic HttpStatusCode Example/VB/source.vb#1)]

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype System.Net.HttpStatusCode Ambiguous = int32(300)

Docs.summary: Equivalent to HTTP status 300. indicates that the requested information has multiple representations. The default action is to treat this status as a redirect and follow the contents of the Location header associated with this response.

remarks.format:
## Remarks If the <xref:System.Net.HttpWebRequest.AllowAutoRedirect%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property is `false`, Ambiguous will cause an exception to be thrown.
Ambiguous is a synonym for MultipleChoices.
